What is the value of `x` after the following code executes?

```java
int x = 10;
x += 4;
x -= 3;
```

What is printed when the following code executes?

```java
int n = 6;
n *= 2;
n -= 4;
System.out.println(n);
```

What is printed when the following code executes?

```java
int x = 17;
x %= 5;
System.out.println(x);
```

What is printed when the following code executes?

```java
int x = 7;
x /= 2;
System.out.println(x);
```

What is the value of `sum` after the following code executes?

```java
int sum = 0;
for (int i = 1; i <= 4; i++) {
    sum += i;
}
```

What is printed when the following code executes?

```java
int a = 20;
int b = 3;
a /= b;
a += b;
System.out.println(a);
```

What is printed when the following code executes?

```java
int x = 1;
while (x < 50) {
    x *= 3;
}
System.out.println(x);
```

A student intends to add each value of `i` to `sum` as the loop runs. What is the value of `sum` after the following code executes?

```java
int sum = 0;
for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
    sum =+ i;
}
```

What is printed when the following code executes?

```java
int a = 4;
a += a * a;
System.out.println(a);
```

What is printed when the following code executes?

```java
int total = 7;
total /= 2;
total *= 2;
System.out.println(total);
```

Determine the value of `x` after the following code runs.

```java
int x = 10;
x += 3;
x -= 4;
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int n = 17;
n /= 5;
System.out.println(n);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int balance = 100;
balance =- 20;
System.out.println(balance);
```

Determine the values of `a` and `b` after the following code runs.

```java
int a = 5;
int b = 3;
a += b;
b *= a;
```

Determine the value of `x` after the following code runs.

```java
int x = 10;
x -= 3;
x *= 2;
```

Determine the value of `n` after the following code runs.

```java
int n = 25;
n %= 7;
n += 10;
```

Determine the output of the following code.

```java
int total = 10;
for (int i = 1; i <= 4; i++) {
    total -= i;
}
System.out.println(total);
```

The following code is intended to print the sum of the integers from 1 through 5 (which is 15), but it does not. Which of the following correctly identifies the bug?

```java
int sum = 0;
for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
    sum =+ i;
}
System.out.println(sum);
```

Determine the values of `x` and `y` after the following code runs.

```java
int x = 15;
int y = 4;
x /= y;
y += x;
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 18;
int y = 5;

x -= y * 2;
y += x / 3;
x *= y - 4;
x %= y;

System.out.println(x + " " + y);
```

Determine the values of `a` and `b` after the following code runs.

```java
int a = 9;
int b = 4;

a += b;
b *= 2;
a -= b / 3;
b %= a - 5;
```
